# Mobile Architecture

## The Rule

All mobile development happens in `frontend/`. The iOS and Android apps are
Capacitor wrappers around the production web app at `https://dealgapiq.com`.
There is **no separate mobile codebase**. There is no `mobile/` directory.

## How It Works

The Capacitor WebView loads the Vercel-deployed web app. The same React
components, hooks, and styles render on both web and mobile. Platform-specific
behavior is gated at runtime via `IS_CAPACITOR` from `src/lib/env.ts`.

```
Web browser ──► https://dealgapiq.com (Vercel) ──► React app
Capacitor ─────► WKWebView / WebView loads same URL ──► same React app
                 + native bridge (deep links, IAP, status bar, splash)
```

## Key Files

| Purpose | Path |
|---|---|
| Capacitor config | `frontend/capacitor.config.ts` |
| Runtime detection | `frontend/src/lib/env.ts` (`IS_CAPACITOR`) |
| Deep link handler | `frontend/src/hooks/useCapacitorDeepLinks.ts` |
| Shell UX (status bar, splash, external links) | `frontend/src/hooks/useCapacitorShell.ts` |
| In-app purchases (RevenueCat) | `frontend/src/hooks/useRevenueCat.ts` |
| Bridge initializer | `frontend/src/app/providers.tsx` (`CapacitorBridge`) |
| Build script | `frontend/scripts/build-capacitor.sh` |
| Local dev script | `frontend/scripts/cap-dev.sh` |
| iOS native project | `frontend/ios/` |
| Android native project | `frontend/android/` |

## Capacitor-Gated Code Pattern

```typescript
import { IS_CAPACITOR } from '@/lib/env'

if (IS_CAPACITOR) {
  // Native-only behavior (deep links, IAP, status bar, etc.)
} else {
  // Web-only behavior (Stripe checkout, cookie auth, etc.)
}
```

## Forbidden Patterns

```
mobile/                          ← DELETED — do not create or reference
react-native                     ← do not install or import
expo                             ← do not install or import
@react-navigation                ← do not install or import
mobile/app/verdict.tsx           ← does not exist
mobile/components/               ← does not exist
```

Do NOT create a `mobile/` directory. Do NOT use React Native, Expo, or any
native-specific UI framework. All UI is web-standard HTML/CSS/React rendered
inside the Capacitor WebView.

## When Adding Mobile-Specific Behavior

1. Check if `IS_CAPACITOR` already gates the relevant code path
2. If not, add a conditional branch using `IS_CAPACITOR`
3. Keep all code in `frontend/src/` — never create a parallel directory
4. For native plugin access, import from `@capacitor/*` packages
5. Test both web and Capacitor builds after changes
